{{Infobox VG | image = IT Manager 3 - Unseen Forces Logo.png | image_size = 255px | caption = | genre = [[Simulation game|Simulation]] | platform = [[Browser game|Web browser]] | developer = [[Intel Corporation]] | publisher = [[Intel Corporation]] | released = {{vgrelease|WW|2009}} }}
'''''IT Manager III: Unseen Forces''''' was a web-based [[information technology]] (IT) simulation game from [[Intel]] in which the player managed an IT department in a corporate environment.
There were two aspects to the game. Firstly, the player had to ensure that employees' desktop PCs, laptops and servers kept running smoothly. There were dozens of software and hardware faults to tackle of varying complexity.
As the player's company grew, it placed increasing demands on IT departments, and the player had to ensure that the technologies were rolled out to take the strain. This gave the game a second strategic dimension. Upgraded and new technologies reduced maintenance costs, increased security and made employees happier and more productive.
The game spanned eight levels. Each represented a bigger office than the last, and the IT issues were more challenging. If the player could improve productivity whilst maintaining a good working environment, the company's share price would go up. When it hit its target value, the level would be complete.
IT Manager III is no longer online. In July 2012, it was replaced by its successor, the multiplayer [[IT Manager: Duels]].
== Awards ==
IT Manager III: Unseen Forces was shortlisted for the NMA effectiveness awards in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nmaawards.co.uk/Shortlist.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-07-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120915064920/http://www.nmaawards.co.uk/Shortlist.aspx |archivedate=2012-09-15 |df= }}</ref> It won the 2009 British Interactive Media Association award in the best business-to-business category<ref>http://www.prlog.org/10425726-mrm-london-wins-2009-bima-award.html</ref> and the Intel Innovation Grand Prix award 2011, which Intel acknowledges a top supplier.<ref>http://www.btobonline.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20121008/AGENCIES02/310089937/direct-agency-of-the-year-mrm-blends-technology-creativity&template=printart</ref>
